---
layout: base.njk
title: Web Everything — Validation Rules (see)
---

<div class="page-sheet">

<section class="intro">
  <h1>Validation Rules</h1>
  <p>
    A <strong>zero-lock-in</strong> devtool that adapts to the validation tools you
    <em>already</em> use. It reads each incumbent's own config — ESLint, Oxlint — and normalizes
    them into one internal pivot model, then shows you a single unified list of every concern your
    tools cover. You can run it once and stop: the project keeps <strong>no reference</strong> to it
    whatsoever (it only ever touches the incumbents' own config files).
  </p>
  <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted);">
    This page is the <strong>see</strong> leg of the
    <a href="/backlog/236-validation-normalization-shopping-devtool/">adapter-as-normalization-hub</a>.
    <strong>Re-export</strong> (emit the equivalent config for a different tool) and
    <strong>shop</strong> (pick tools by the validation you want) are deferred to follow-up items.
  </p>
</section>

<section style="margin: 1rem 0 2rem; display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 1.5rem;">
  {% set stat = [
    { n: validationRules.summary.concerns, l: 'concerns' },
    { n: validationRules.summary.active, l: 'enforced here' },
    { n: validationRules.summary.divergences, l: 'divergent across tools' },
    { n: validationRules.summary.noEquivalentCells, l: 'no-equivalent cells' }
  ] %}
  {% for s in stat %}
  <div>
    <div style="font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1;">{{ s.n }}</div>
    <div style="font-size: 0.8em; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; color: var(--color-text-muted);">{{ s.l }}</div>
  </div>
  {% endfor %}
</section>

<section style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem; padding: 0.75rem 1rem; border-left: 3px solid var(--color-border); background: var(--color-surface, #fafafa); font-size: 0.9em;">
  <strong>The lossiness is the product.</strong> Cross-tool rule semantics are not 1:1. Each cell is
  tagged with a confidence grade, and the <em>no-equivalent</em> cells — where a tool simply can't
  express a concern — are the most useful for choosing tools, not the embarrassing ones.
</section>

<we-data-table><table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.92em; background: #fff;">
  <thead>
    <tr style="text-align: left; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-border);">
      <th style="padding: 0.6rem 0.75rem; width: 38%;">Concern</th>
      {% for t in validationRules.tools %}
      <th style="padding: 0.6rem 0.75rem;">{{ t.name }}</th>
      {% endfor %}
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    {% for row in validationRules.model %}
    <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); {% if row.divergence %}background: rgba(255, 196, 0, 0.06);{% endif %}">
      <td style="padding: 0.7rem 0.75rem; vertical-align: top;">
        <div style="font-weight: 600;">
          {{ row.label }}
          {% if row.activeInProject %}<span title="Enforced by at least one of your tools" style="color: var(--color-accent, #2563eb); font-size: 0.85em;">● enforced</span>{% endif %}
        </div>
        <div style="color: var(--color-text-muted); margin: 0.2rem 0;">{{ row.description }}</div>
        <code style="display: block; font-size: 0.85em; background: var(--color-surface, #f5f5f5); padding: 0.3rem 0.5rem; border-radius: 4px; white-space: pre-wrap;">{{ row.catches }}</code>
      </td>
      {% for cell in row.cells %}
      <td style="padding: 0.7rem 0.75rem; vertical-align: top;">
        {% if not cell.covered %}
          <span style="color: #b45309; font-weight: 600;">— no equivalent</span>
          <div style="font-size: 0.82em; color: var(--color-text-muted);">This tool can't express the concern.</div>
        {% else %}
          <div>
            {% if cell.active %}
              <span title="severity: {{ cell.severity }}" style="color: var(--color-accent, #2563eb);">✓ enforced</span>
              <span style="color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.85em;">({{ cell.severity }})</span>
            {% else %}
              <span style="color: var(--color-text-muted);">○ available, off</span>
            {% endif %}
          </div>
          <code style="font-size: 0.82em;">{{ cell.rule }}</code>
          <div style="font-size: 0.78em; margin-top: 0.2rem;">
            <span style="display: inline-block; padding: 0.05rem 0.4rem; border-radius: 9999px; font-size: 0.85em; background: {% if cell.confidence == 'exact' %}rgba(34,197,94,0.15){% elif cell.confidence == 'partial' %}rgba(234,179,8,0.18){% else %}rgba(148,163,184,0.18){% endif %};">{{ cell.confidence }}</span>
          </div>
          {% if cell.note %}<div style="font-size: 0.78em; color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-top: 0.2rem;">{{ cell.note }}</div>{% endif %}
        {% endif %}
      </td>
      {% endfor %}
    </tr>
    {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table></we-data-table>

</div>
